nd its perceptions of gender, from the ground up. From the artist who defied the junta to hand out sanitary towels at her exhibition, to the Muslim campaigner who has already spent a quarter of her life in prison; from the feminist Buddhist nun to the pop star who gets called a whore for performing; these are the voices of The Other Ladies of Myanmar.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aThe Other Ladies of Myanmar. 0aWomenzBurmaxSocial conditions. 0aWomen's rightszBurma. 0aWomen, BurmesevBiography. 0aWomen—Myanmar—Social condition. 0aWomen’s rights—Myanmar. 4aWomen's Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060677540uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981481826140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814818261423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814818261.jpg  a978-3-11-060677-5  ISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-071955-0  DG Plus eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK